  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05/D3 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package embeds adversarial weakness W-AR-05 (comparator absence/mismatch) via defeater type D3 (undercutting — inference method mismatch): the primary validation result omits its comparedAgainst link, and a secondary result references a comparator dataset acquired under ventricular-assist-device (VAD) operating conditions rather than CPB flow-speed regimes, a distinction discussed positively but without rigorous applicability scrutiny.",
