    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required Gradation 2 levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out at Gradation 1 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4 for a Class II device at MRL 2. The primary validation result demonstrates CFD-predicted NIH values consistent with published CPB hemolysis literature, and the secondary validation result against the VAD comparator dataset shows agreement within 18 % — accepted as satisfactory for Gradation 2. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion is met at all five CPB operating points. The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD model has sufficient credibility to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB COU, and the submission is accepted for regulatory filing.",
